  "description": "Variation of condition 1 approved drawings for planning permission reference number 21/AP/3568: Variation of a Condition 1 Approved drawings  for planning permission reference number: 19/AP/1116 dated 18/10/2019 for demolition of existing public house (Use Class A4) and construction of new, four storey plus basement mixed-used building comprising basement and ground floor drinking establishment (Use Class A4) with 8 residential units (x4 studio flats, x3 one bedroom flats and x1 two bedroom flat) (Use Class C3) on first, second and third floor levels with balcony amenity spaces and associated cycle and refuse storage.\rCondition 1 to be varied to reference the amended plans to include:\r\r- To increase the height of the building by 1.27m to increase the internal floor to ceiling heights of each unit from 2.4m to 2.5m.\r- Addition of louvres to add ventilation ot the commercial unit\r- Reduction of the commerical floorspace from 120sqm to 113sqm to allow for wall construction and plant equipment. \r- Increase in the basement floor height from 2.4m to 2.5m, reduction of the basement floor area from 148sqm to 124sqm. \r- The cast stone cladding is to be replaced with white brickwork  \r- The cast stone sills and coping will be replaced with PPC aluminium coping and sills in a colour to match the glazing\r- Amendment to location and size of the AOV and roof access; \r- Provision of 2no. condenser units at roof level; \r-  Reduction in size of amenity areas to flats 3, 6 and 8 by 1 sqm \r- Reduction in size of amenity area to flat 7 by 0.5 sqm.\rCondition 9 to be confirmed to reflect the findings in the Noise Report.",
